<br/>
Chongqing is often seen as a neon-soaked cyberpunk city, but her guide shows the other side: a softer, more natural rhythm. Evening walks and breezes on E’gongyan Bridge, the cinematic double-loop interchange at Rongqiao Nankai Middle School, the dizzying heights of Caiyuanba Bridge, her childhood home in Geleshan Town, and late-night barbecue and bike rides along Binjiang Road in Nan’an District. These spots reveal a Chongqing of open skies, riversides, and mountain paths, far from the clichés.<br/>
<br/>
Follow @RADII_media for the ultimate city guide across Asia, uncovering underground scenes and secret spots.<br/>
